com.rcextract.minecord

Class Channel

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rcextract.minecord.Channel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RecordManager<ChannelEvent>

    public class Channel
extends Object
implements RecordManager<ChannelEvent>
    In Minecord, a Channel groups up a set of users, usually by small topic of a big topic. Main settings and customizations are done in the server, but a channel can has its own settings and customizations, unfollowing the server.

    Both identifier and name are primary keys for developers and users to refer so they are unique. Identifier is unchangeable, name is changeable but must not be used by other channels. However, channels with the same identifier or name can appear in different servers.

    If locked, all players are kicked from the channel and no one can join it. Only players with custom permission MANAGE_CHANNELS can access, lock or unlock the channel.

    A ChannelRecordManager helps a server to manage records. It is separated into a class for merging purposes which feature will be provided in the future.
